SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYSaturday 30 April S10 V3 Having won the DStv Premiership on Wednesday, Mamelodi Sundowns now look for a place in the final on the Nedbank Cup when they take on Royal AM in Durban on Saturday. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Newcastle United vs Liverpool: Newcastle have won four games in a row as their turnaround under Eddie Howe continues, including three at home. Liverpool must win to keep up pressure on leaders Manchester City.M2 Cagliari vs Hellas Verona: Relegation threatened Cagliari have won only one of their previous seven meetings against VeronaM3 Kaizer Chiefs vs Cape Town City: Catch up game from December when Chiefs had COVID-19 cases. Chiefs have lost both games since Stuart Baxter was fired.M4 VfB Stuttgart vs VfL Wolfsburg: Stuttgart won 2-0 away at Wolfsburg earlier this season and desperately need another three points if they are to avoid relegation from the Bundesliga.M5 Aston Villa vs Norwich City: Villa have collected a solitary point from their past five Premier League matches. Norwich are running out of games to save their top flight status.M6 Southampton vs Crystal Palace: Southampton have won one of their previous four home games against Palace with two draws and a defeat.M7 Watford vs Burnley: Potential relegation dogfight as Watford have lost their last four games and Burnley are seeking a revival after sacking manager Sean Dyche.M8 Wolverhampton Wanderers vs Brighton & Hove Albion: Wolves have won their last two meetings against Brighton. Before that they had played out four successive draws in their head-to-head clashes.M9 Leeds United vs Manchester City: Champions Man City beat Leeds 7-0 at home in December but have not won a game at Elland Road since 2000.M10 Royal AM vs Mamelodi Sundowns: Nedbank Cup semi-final between the teams who are in the top two places in the league standings. In their only previous clash in December, Sundowns won 3-2 at home. Suggested permutation:R32.00 3 x 2, 3 x 2, 3 x 2, 3 x 1 x 1 x 2, 3 x 1 x 3 x 3